SIMPLE: flip
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flip
<hw>Flip</hw> <pr>(fl⟦icr⟧p)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Prov. E.
<ets>flip</ets> nimble, flippant, also, a slight blow. Cf.
<er>Flippant</er>.]</ety> <def>A mixture of beer, spirit, etc., stirred
and heated by a hot iron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Flip dog</b></col>, <cd>an iron used, when heated, to
warm flip.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flip</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Flip
<hw>Flip</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Flipped</conjf> <pr>(fl⟦icr⟧pt)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Flipping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To toss (an object)
into the air so as make it turn over one or more times; to fillip;
<as>as, to <ex>flip</ex> up a cent</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As when your little ones⟦br⟧
Do 'twixt their fingers <qex>flip</qex> their cherry stones.</q>
<rj><qau>W. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To turn (a flat object) over with a quick motion;
<as>as, to <ex>flip</ex> a card over; to <ex>flip</ex> a
pancake</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To cause (a person) to turn against former
colleagues, such as to become a witness for the state, in a criminal
prosecution in which the person is a defendant.</def>
<mark>[cant]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Finance)</fld> <def>To resell (an asset) rapidly to
make a quick profit.</def> <mark>[cant]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flip</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Flip
<hw>Flip</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Flipped</conjf> <pr>(fl⟦icr⟧pt)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Flipping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To become insane or irrational;
-- often used with <ptcl>out</ptcl>; <as>as, seeing her mother killed
made the girl <ex>flip out</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flipe</ent>⟦br⟧
